    <div class="content-box">
        <h3>Introduction</h3>
        <div class="img-bio">
            <p>Odisha, the land of temples, traditions, and timeless beauty, lies along the eastern coast of India, embracing the vast Bay of Bengal. It is a place where history meets spirituality, where nature dances in its purest form, and where every heart beats with a rhythm of devotion and culture. The very soil of Odisha carries the echoes of ancient empires, brave warriors, and poets who shaped its identity. Home to millions, it stands as a testimony to resilience, art, and a legacy that continues to inspire generations.With its capital in Bhubaneswar, often called the "Temple City of India," Odisha is a treasure trove of history, culture, and natural beauty. From the serene beaches of Puri to the bustling streets of Cuttack, this state is a harmonious blend of tradition and modernity.</p>
            <img src="https://www.honeymoonbug.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/Odisha-1.jpg" alt="img">
