<div class="content-box">
    <h3>Economy & Industries</h3>
    <div class="img-bio">
        <p>Odisha stands as a powerhouse of natural resources, with abundant reserves of coal, iron ore, and bauxite driving its industrial growth. The IT sector in Bhubaneswar is expanding rapidly, shaping the city into a smart hub of technology and innovation. Agriculture remains the backbone, with lush paddy fields and vibrant handloom industries producing world-famous Sambalpuri sarees, keeping tradition alive in modern times.The Rourkela Steel Plant stands as a symbol of industrial growth, while the Paradip Port connects Odisha to global trade. Yet, amidst this progress, the state remains deeply rooted in its agrarian traditions, with rice being the lifeline of its rural economy. Odisha’s journey is one of balancing modernity with sustainability, ensuring a brighter future for its people.</p>
        <img src="https://indianindustryplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/petro_chemical1.jpg" alt="img">
    </div>
</div>
<!-- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -->
<div class="content-box">
    <h3>Education and Infrastructure</h3>
    <div class="img-bio">
        <p>Odisha is a land of learning and progress. Institutions like IIT Bhubaneswar and NIT Rourkela are beacons of knowledge, nurturing the dreams of countless students. The state’s infrastructure is evolving rapidly, with smart city projects transforming Bhubaneswar into a hub of innovation. The Paradip Port and a network of highways and railways connect Odisha to the world, fostering trade and development. Yet, amidst this growth, the state remains committed to preserving its cultural and natural heritage, ensuring a balanced and sustainable future.</p>
        <img src="https://www.netsgurukul.com/public/images/blog_image/20805_Day%20Boarding%20School%20in%20Odisha.jpg" alt="img">
    </div>
</div>
