<div class="content-box">
    <h3>Food</h3>
    <div class="img-bio">
        <p>Odisha’s cuisine is a celebration of flavors, simplicity, and love. The humble Pakhala Bhata, a fermented rice dish, is a comfort food that reflects the state’s agrarian roots. The sweet delight of Rasagola, a soft and spongy dessert, has won hearts across the world. From the spicy Chhena Poda to the wholesome Dalma, every dish is a reflection of Odisha’s rich culinary heritage. The aroma of street food like Gupchup and Bara fills the air, reminding you that food here is not just sustenance; it’s an expression of joy and togetherness.</p>
        <img src="https://nomadsaikat.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Food-of-Odisha.webp" alt="img">
    </div>
</div>
