<div class="content-box">
    <h3>Natural Resources and Environment</h3>
    <div class="img-bio">
        <p>Odisha’s natural beauty is as diverse as its culture. The dense forests of Simlipal and the mangroves of Bhitarkanika are sanctuaries for wildlife, while the Chilika Lake teems with life, from playful dolphins to migratory birds. The state’s mineral wealth, including bauxite and coal, fuels its industrial growth. Yet, Odisha faces challenges like cyclones and coastal erosion, reminding us of the delicate balance between development and conservation. The people of Odisha, with their resilience and reverence for nature, strive to protect this land of abundance.</p>
